data.notes: This was my attempt at capturing the total lunar eclipse of March 2025. Unfortunately, clouds rolled in as totality approached, ruining my night.

This 43-megapixel panorama provides a view of the terminator of the waxing gibbous Moon shortly after sunrise at some of the Moon's largest craters and mountains. Dramatic shadows are cast on Plato crater in the north, Copernicus crater near the equator, and Tycho crater near the south pole.
